text:
The Four Types of AgentRun
The AgentRun type is a Union of four different execution patterns:

from lasagna import (
    # These are the unioned types:
    AgentRunMessageList,
    AgentRunParallel,
    AgentRunChained,
    AgentRunExtraction,
)


1. AgentRunMessageList â€” Standard Conversation
This is the most common type â€” a simple conversation between human and AI.

simple_conversation: AgentRunMessageList = {
    "type": "messages",
    "agent": "my_chat_agent",  # â† agent name can be anything you want!
    "messages": [
        {"role": "human", "text": "Hello!"},
        {"role": "ai", "text": "Hi there! How can I help?"},
    ],
}



2. AgentRunParallel â€” Concurrent Execution
Used when an agent spawns multiple sub-agents to work simultaneously (in parallel).

parallel_subagents: AgentRunParallel = {
    "type": "parallel",
    "agent": "committee_agent",  # â† agent name can be anything you want!
    "runs": [
        # Multiple AgentRuns that executed in parallel:
        # {...}, {...}, {...}
    ],
}



3. AgentRunChained â€” Sequential Execution
Used when an agent coordinates a sequence of sub-agents (â€œchained subagentsâ€).

chained_subagents: AgentRunChained = {
    "type": "chain",
    "agent": "pipeline_agent",  # â† agent name can be anything you want!
    "runs": [
        # AgentRuns that executed one after another:
        # {...}, {...}, {...}
    ],
}



4. AgentRunExtraction â€” Structured Output
Used when an agent extracts structured data from its input.

extracted_info: AgentRunExtraction = {
    "type": "extraction",
    "agent": "data_extractor",  # â† agent name can be anything you want!
    "messages": [
        # Model's generated messages will be here.
        # Consider this an implementation detail; see the `result` below
        # for the actual "extraction result".
    ],
    "result": {
        # This is the payload that was extracted:
        "name": "John Doe",
        "email": "john@example.com", 
        "age": 30,
    },
}
